docs.abstract: The Memorial Arch, a granite monument to soldiers and sailors in the plaza, is about to get desperately needed restoration work.
docs.snippet: The Memorial Arch, a granite monument to soldiers and sailors in the plaza, is about to get desperately needed restoration work.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the moments after the Presidential election was called in favor of Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Nov. 7, a jubilant crowd gathered spontaneously in Brooklyn’s Grand Army Plaza, whooping and dancing around the Soldiers’ and Sailors’ Memorial Arch, atop which the bronze allegorical figure of Columbia, representing America, thundered forth in her horse-drawn chariot, flanked by trumpeting figures of winged Victory.

headline.main: In Brooklyn, Grand Army Plaza Gets an Intervention

docs.abstract: The comments by the United Nations Human Rights Committee come as the Trump administration faces growing criticism for deploying federal agents to confront Black Lives Matter protesters.
docs.snippet: The comments by the United Nations Human Rights Committee come as the Trump administration faces growing criticism for deploying federal agents to confront Black Lives Matter protesters.
docs.lead_paragraph: GENEVA — Law-enforcement authorities are obligated to protect and facilitate peaceful demonstrations, an influential United Nations human rights panel said on Wednesday, challenging tactics the police have used against anti-racism protests in American cities and around the world.

headline.main: U.N. Panel Takes Aim at Heavy-Handed Police Tactics at Protests
headline.print_headline: U.N. Panel Criticizes Heavy-Handed Tactics Used by Police at Protests

docs.abstract: As injuries mount, teams are turning to passers with thin résumés. The results have not been pretty.
docs.snippet: As injuries mount, teams are turning to passers with thin résumés. The results have not been pretty.
docs.lead_paragraph: Ben Barnett, a quarterback coach based in Oregon, watches a lot of N.F.L. games with his hands practically covering his eyes. It saves him from seeing protracted throwing motions, hopelessly misaligned hips and shoulders, and other mechanical injustices he has spotted among the league’s growing list of struggling passers.

headline.main: N.F.L. Is Full of Quarterbacks Who Are Off the Mark, or Even Off the Street
headline.print_headline: These Passers Have Offensive Skills. Not in a Good Way.

docs.abstract: The city had faced criticism over plans to pay social media influencers $2,000 each to fight misinformation during the trials of Derek Chauvin and three other former police officers charged in George Floyd’s death.
docs.snippet: The city had faced criticism over plans to pay social media influencers $2,000 each to fight misinformation during the trials of Derek Chauvin and three other former police officers charged in George Floyd’s death.
docs.lead_paragraph: The City of Minneapolis has abandoned a contentious plan to pay social media influencers $2,000 each to help it combat misinformation during the upcoming trials of four police officers charged in the killing of George Floyd, officials said on Monday.

headline.main: Minneapolis Abandons Plan to Pay Influencers During Officers’ Trials

docs.abstract: Goya, Caravaggio, Rubens, Velázquez and more are in skylit splendor in the European galleries. And the museum is acknowledging the shaping force on art of colonialism, slavery, the disenfranchisement of women.

docs.lead_paragraph: “In a dark time, the eye begins to see,” the poet wrote. And after the dark, dark time we’ve been through, this year’s winter solstice, marking the start of slow climb back into light, may carry more metaphorical weight than usual.

headline.main: The Met Casts New Light on its Greatest Hits and History
